# Rover

- Canonical docs live under `docs/` (conceptual-core, OPERATING-MODEL, open-decisions).
- Do not invent permissions, consent, corpus rights, or funding facts.
- Do not commit training corpora, CAD/HTML chassis mockups, or large binaries unless an issue explicitly asks.
- Soft public naming: Fielding OK; no full literary homage until permission lands. Corpus = intent only.
- Private boundary: funder-restricted application content, personal fallback finances, LBI consent-sensitive material.
- Dual license: CC BY 4.0 (docs), Apache-2.0 (software). See LICENSE.
- Prefer label `software` over `firmware`.
- Avoid the word "master" in new user-facing text, docs, comments, and identifiers.
- Foundation then Milestone 1 (Concept & feasibility) — no due dates required unless the artist sets them.
